WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.835 --> 00:00:03.336
<i>Sight will return.</i>

2
00:00:03.420 --> 00:00:05.630
And the first nation to harness its powers

3
00:00:05.714 --> 00:00:07.382
will be the nation
that dominates the world.

4
00:00:08.926 --> 00:00:11.010
Baba Voss. I'm taking you to Haniwa.

5
00:00:11.094 --> 00:00:13.805
If you're planning to fight your way out.
you could use all the hands you can get.

6
00:00:13.889 --> 00:00:15.807
<i>God had a plan for me</i>

7
00:00:15.891 --> 00:00:21.755
to consecrate the city of Pennsa
as the new capital of the Payan kingdom.

8
00:00:22.189 --> 00:00:23.857
<i>I told Harlan you would marry him.</i>

9
00:00:23.941 --> 00:00:25.316
<i>It's a business arrangement.</i>

10
00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:28.862
You've spent time with the queen.
Be very careful.

11
00:00:28.946 --> 00:00:31.906
Kofun. This is Tormada.
one of our greatest scientists.

12
00:00:31.990 --> 00:00:34.768
Put aside your grief. Oloman.
You work for him now.

13
00:00:35.244 --> 00:00:38.705
The Trivantians are consumed
with the war with the Ganites to the west.

14
00:00:38.789 --> 00:00:40.582
Do nothing to draw
their attention to the east.

15
00:00:40.666 --> 00:00:41.708
What if it's too late for that?

16
00:00:41.792 --> 00:00:45.820
I will convince the council to request
a diplomatic summit.

17
00:00:46.255 --> 00:00:49.507
We accept your proposal and thank you
on behalf of the Payan people.

18
00:00:49.591 --> 00:00:50.967
We've been betrayed!

19
00:00:53.512 --> 00:00:54.554
Sibeth.

20
00:00:54.638 --> 00:00:56.055
She was never gonna allow a treaty.

21
00:00:56.139 --> 00:00:59.726
My ladies and lords. we're now at war.

22
00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:01.519
The Witchfinders will not fight for you.

23
00:01:01.603 --> 00:01:04.606
My Witchfinders will do as I say.
They're my army.

24
00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:07.926
No. They are my army.

25
00:01:08.819 --> 00:01:09.736
Tak!

26
00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:10.820
Tak! Tak! Tak!

27
00:01:10.904 --> 00:01:13.306
So it's a coup?

28
00:01:13.782 --> 00:01:17.060
Wait! She is with child.

29
00:01:17.619 --> 00:01:19.037
I'm nobody's father.

30
00:01:19.121 --> 00:01:21.623
Green hill Gap. We'll make our stand there.

31
00:01:21.707 --> 00:01:24.109
Advance!

32
00:01:24.626 --> 00:01:26.319
We are Payan soldiers.

33
00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:28.338
<i>mountain warriors.</i>

34
00:01:28.422 --> 00:01:31.674
<i>Former enemies banded together
for one purpose only:</i>

35
00:01:31.758 --> 00:01:35.303
<i>To protect what is ours at all costs!</i>

36
00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:39.933
<i>We were raised as warriors.</i>

37
00:01:40.017 --> 00:01:42.143
<i>It's always been our fate
to die like this.</i>

38
00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:45.730
<i>Is there anything I can say
to convince you to come back with me?</i>

39
00:01:45.814 --> 00:01:47.857
My home… I couldn't leave them.

40
00:01:47.941 --> 00:01:49.943
- Kofun.
- Maghra.

41
00:01:50.027 --> 00:01:51.152
<i>The world has changed.</i>

42
00:01:51.236 --> 00:01:55.490
and in this new world
there are no longer any Witchfinders.

43
00:01:55.574 --> 00:01:57.951
Oloman. You have a demonstration for me.

44
00:01:58.035 --> 00:01:59.227
Wait for it.

45
00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:07.001
I will kill this child
before I let it be taken.

46
00:02:07.085 --> 00:02:08.752
This war isn't over. Baba.

47
00:02:08.836 --> 00:02:10.322
<i>It is for me.</i>

48
00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:18.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

49
00:02:33.384 --> 00:02:34.968
Shields up!

50
00:03:00.035 --> 00:03:01.536
Hold position!

51
00:03:01.620 --> 00:03:02.729
Hold!

52
00:03:12.965 --> 00:03:14.700
Shield formation!

53
00:03:16.093 --> 00:03:21.123
Hold the line! Hold...

54
00:03:32.818 --> 00:03:35.304
Hold! Hold them back!

55
00:03:41.035 --> 00:03:43.620
There's too many of them.

56
00:03:43.704 --> 00:03:45.038
Fall back!

57
00:03:45.122 --> 00:03:47.107
Go! Go!

58
00:04:14.151 --> 00:04:15.427
Let's go!

59
00:05:53.709 --> 00:05:55.027
Drop the gate.

60
00:06:09.517 --> 00:06:13.270
How glorious
the pain of childbirth. Maghra.

61
00:06:13.354 --> 00:06:15.772
Ah. you never told me.

62
00:06:15.856 --> 00:06:17.190
You forget quickly.

63
00:06:17.274 --> 00:06:19.025
Liar.

64
00:06:20.361 --> 00:06:22.612
- Queen.
- What?

65
00:06:22.696 --> 00:06:24.239
Queen.

66
00:06:24.323 --> 00:06:25.557
What is it?

67
00:06:26.450 --> 00:06:30.479
There's still no birth water. only blood.
Too much blood.

68
00:06:38.629 --> 00:06:40.589
- Try and be calm and...
- Oh. you be calm.

69
00:06:40.673 --> 00:06:46.286
I'm being torn open from the inside out.

70
00:06:46.679 --> 00:06:49.347
- Help her to her feet.
- No.

71
00:06:49.431 --> 00:06:50.599
- Yes.
- No.

72
00:06:50.683 --> 00:06:51.833
Yes. Sibeth.

73
00:06:53.394 --> 00:06:54.503
Come on.

74
00:06:56.814 --> 00:06:59.424
Yes. Yes.

75
00:07:00.192 --> 00:07:03.470
Straps. Bend.

76
00:07:04.947 --> 00:07:07.140
Yes.

77
00:07:08.909 --> 00:07:10.143
And the other one.

78
00:07:11.328 --> 00:07:12.437
All right.

79
00:07:18.627 --> 00:07:22.047
Sibeth. I need you to stop pushing.

80
00:07:22.131 --> 00:07:23.173
I can't!

81
00:07:23.257 --> 00:07:26.176
You must. The baby is still in its veil.

82
00:07:26.260 --> 00:07:29.471
It must be born in its water sack
or risk having no breath.

83
00:07:29.555 --> 00:07:32.557
So get it out with the sack!

84
00:07:32.641 --> 00:07:34.184
Wait.

85
00:07:37.855 --> 00:07:42.092
I'm protecting it. Now... Now push.

86
00:07:43.444 --> 00:07:44.553
Push!

87
00:07:49.784 --> 00:07:50.784
Yes.

88
00:08:09.970 --> 00:08:11.079
Harmony.

89
00:08:12.348 --> 00:08:15.809
Why do I hear nothing? Make my baby cry.

90
00:08:15.893 --> 00:08:17.628
We are trying.

91
00:08:45.422 --> 00:08:49.509
It's a boy.

92
00:08:53.264 --> 00:08:56.541
A veiled birth is a good omen.
a baby consecrated by water.

93
00:08:59.645 --> 00:09:03.548
God Flame has blessed me
with a sighted prophet.

94
00:09:05.484 --> 00:09:10.138
We'll name him Wolffe after our father.

95
00:09:17.288 --> 00:09:18.814
He's hungry.

96
00:09:19.290 --> 00:09:21.233
Maghra. please let me feed him.

97
00:09:22.835 --> 00:09:24.778
We have a wet nurse ready for that.

98
00:09:30.593 --> 00:09:33.328
You would deny the baby
his mother's milk? Huh?

99
00:09:33.721 --> 00:09:35.330
Don't start. Sibeth.

100
00:09:44.064 --> 00:09:47.050
A queen who can deliver a baby.

101
00:09:48.277 --> 00:09:51.179
I forgot you once were an Alkenny peasant.

102
00:09:51.989 --> 00:09:53.724
It was Paris who taught me.

103
00:09:54.700 --> 00:09:58.145
And you would do well remembering her name
when you ask for sympathy.

104
00:09:58.788 --> 00:10:01.581
That mountain woman wanted
to take my baby.

105
00:10:01.665 --> 00:10:03.734
Well. now I am taking your baby.

106
00:10:04.251 --> 00:10:05.986
Are you going to kill me as well?

107
00:10:09.465 --> 00:10:10.674
You never know.

108
00:10:10.758 --> 00:10:12.551
- My queen.
- Already?

109
00:10:12.635 --> 00:10:15.303
- Time is of the essence.
- I told him he was rushing things.

110
00:10:15.387 --> 00:10:17.915
- You said the time was now.
- I was being ironic.

111
00:10:18.516 --> 00:10:22.644
Maghra.
clearly this is a deeply emotional moment.

112
00:10:22.728 --> 00:10:23.729
And I know...

113
00:10:23.813 --> 00:10:26.648
The Trivantians will soon know
of the baby.

114
00:10:26.732 --> 00:10:28.108
When Ambassador Trovere arrives.

115
00:10:28.192 --> 00:10:30.402
she'll be expecting
to take custody of Sibeth

116
00:10:30.486 --> 00:10:32.946
to take her trophy back to Trivantes.

117
00:10:33.030 --> 00:10:34.364
These are the terms you agreed to.

118
00:10:34.448 --> 00:10:35.824
There's no stopping him
once he gets...

119
00:10:35.908 --> 00:10:39.645
- Harlan!
- But he's not wrong. strictly speaking.

120
00:10:41.122 --> 00:10:44.166
Maghra. you did promise the Trivantians
your sister once she delivered.

121
00:10:44.250 --> 00:10:46.485
Would either of you like to feed the baby?

122
00:10:48.045 --> 00:10:49.879
No?

123
00:10:49.963 --> 00:10:51.989
Well. then you are
of no use to me right now.

124
00:10:56.178 --> 00:10:57.845
What will you say to Trovere?

125
00:10:59.140 --> 00:11:02.793
Oh. I'm glad you asked. I have no idea.

126
00:11:13.404 --> 00:11:16.807
Thank you. Maghra. Thank you.

127
00:11:17.616 --> 00:11:19.768
Only until the wet nurse arrives.

128
00:11:20.453 --> 00:11:22.062
There you go. little man.

129
00:11:25.374 --> 00:11:26.608
Little Wolffe.

130
00:11:35.968 --> 00:11:37.286
Can you see me?

131
00:11:40.431 --> 00:11:41.790
Can you see your mama?

132
00:11:44.435 --> 00:11:45.544
Hmm?

133
00:11:50.816 --> 00:11:56.305
You're the child of prophecy
sent to me by the God Flame.

134
00:12:12.421 --> 00:12:16.199
Don't you worry.
I will not let them take you from me.

135
00:13:44.889 --> 00:13:48.208
That was our third company retreat
in as many days.

136
00:13:48.684 --> 00:13:50.168
What is happening out there?

137
00:13:50.561 --> 00:13:54.773
They are a bunch of savages.
We are Trivantian soldiers.

138
00:13:54.857 --> 00:13:57.593
They move with the wind. We hear nothing.

139
00:13:57.985 --> 00:13:59.928
And now they know where our camp is.

140
00:14:02.823 --> 00:14:05.183
They're going to find a way down here.

141
00:14:06.035 --> 00:14:08.604
We are outnumbered.
We can't defend this position.

142
00:14:09.622 --> 00:14:11.815
Captain Wren. do you hear yourself?

143
00:14:12.750 --> 00:14:15.377
We were sent here
to quell a primitive uprising.

144
00:14:15.461 --> 00:14:18.213
and instead.
it is turning into a full-scale war.

145
00:14:18.297 --> 00:14:21.033
- And it's a war you're losing.
- Who is that?

146
00:14:21.759 --> 00:14:24.870
Lieutenant Commander Tormada of Base 3.

147
00:14:25.346 --> 00:14:29.182
under the direct command
of the late General Edo Voss.

148
00:14:29.266 --> 00:14:33.729
Tormada. I've heard of you.
Edo's chief scientist.

149
00:14:33.813 --> 00:14:36.273
I didn't think
Base 3 was still operational

150
00:14:36.357 --> 00:14:37.883
after the general's passing.

151
00:14:38.317 --> 00:14:40.610
Wren. you were at Base 3. weren't you?

152
00:14:40.694 --> 00:14:42.554
- Yes. sir.
- Captain Wren.

153
00:14:45.324 --> 00:14:47.017
Edo spoke highly of you.

154
00:14:51.664 --> 00:14:52.898
Thank you. sir.

155
00:14:53.499 --> 00:14:55.817
You were a survivor of Green hill Gap.

156
00:14:58.212 --> 00:15:01.298
Without poor Edo
to shoulder the blame for that defeat.

157
00:15:01.382 --> 00:15:04.826
I imagine there was more than enough
to mete out for everyone else.

158
00:15:05.553 --> 00:15:09.264
It is no doubt why you were exiled here.

159
00:15:09.348 --> 00:15:12.476
My apologies. Lieutenant Commander.

160
00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:16.438
but why would the military send
a scientist out to the front lines?

161
00:15:16.522 --> 00:15:19.508
Because science is
gonna save you. Colonel.

162
00:15:20.442 --> 00:15:22.944
Science is gonna win this war for you.

163
00:15:23.028 --> 00:15:24.237
Wren is right.

164
00:15:24.321 --> 00:15:26.990
The Ganites will be here by morning.
if not sooner.

165
00:15:27.074 --> 00:15:28.116
Well then. my friends.

166
00:15:28.200 --> 00:15:30.952
you will be reporting
complete victory by morning.

167
00:15:31.036 --> 00:15:32.996
With all due respect.
Lieutenant Commander.

168
00:15:33.080 --> 00:15:35.332
you have no idea
what we're up against here.

169
00:15:35.416 --> 00:15:37.484
With all due respect.

170
00:15:38.752 --> 00:15:41.863
you have no idea
what I've brought with me.

171
00:15:44.216 --> 00:15:47.995
♪ <i>Hush. little baby
Don't say a word</i> ♪

172
00:15:48.596 --> 00:15:52.457
♪ <i>Mama's gonna buy you a mockingbird</i> ♪

173
00:15:52.892 --> 00:15:57.087
♪ <i>And if that mockingbird don't sing</i> ♪

174
00:15:57.480 --> 00:16:01.300
♪ <i>Mama's gonna buy you a bell to ring</i> ♪

175
00:16:01.984 --> 00:16:05.971
♪ <i>And if that little bell gets broke</i> ♪

176
00:16:06.363 --> 00:16:09.975
♪ <i>Mama's gonna buy you a billy goat</i> ♪

177
00:16:10.367 --> 00:16:14.146
♪ <i>And if that billy goat won't pull</i> ♪

178
00:16:14.538 --> 00:16:18.250
♪ <i>Mama's gonna buy you a cart and bull</i> ♪

179
00:16:22.046 --> 00:16:23.155
Kofun…

180
00:16:26.425 --> 00:16:27.618
Come.

181
00:16:29.637 --> 00:16:30.871
Hold your son.

182
00:16:34.433 --> 00:16:35.751
I don't know how.

183
00:16:38.187 --> 00:16:41.590
Every parent knows
how to hold their own child.

184
00:16:47.780 --> 00:16:49.389
He is not my child.

185
00:17:18.894 --> 00:17:20.003
Kofun?

186
00:17:22.022 --> 00:17:23.799
Here.

187
00:17:25.901 --> 00:17:27.302
How'd you find me?

188
00:17:27.778 --> 00:17:30.138
Your mom may be queen.
but it's still my city.

189
00:17:30.823 --> 00:17:35.394
Roddy. One for me and another
for my young friend here. please.

190
00:17:41.750 --> 00:17:43.652
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

191
00:17:48.799 --> 00:17:53.261
You know. if Baba Voss were here...

192
00:17:53.345 --> 00:17:54.580
He's not.

193
00:17:55.389 --> 00:17:57.641
No. I know he's not.
Thank you. I'm just saying...

194
00:17:57.725 --> 00:17:58.875
Well. don't.

195
00:18:00.144 --> 00:18:01.269
You might have married his wife.

196
00:18:01.353 --> 00:18:03.581
but that doesn't mean
you're any kind of father to me.

197
00:18:03.814 --> 00:18:05.549
I have enough of those as it is.

198
00:18:06.609 --> 00:18:08.944
I think you know me well enough by now

199
00:18:09.028 --> 00:18:12.489
to know I don't want to be
anybody's father ever. Thank you.

200
00:18:12.573 --> 00:18:13.682
All right.

201
00:18:17.161 --> 00:18:19.938
My own father worked for your grandfather.

202
00:18:21.665 --> 00:18:22.941
He was a good man.

203
00:18:24.335 --> 00:18:29.256
He was very kind.
very fair. very affectionate.

204
00:18:29.340 --> 00:18:30.908
He had this big laugh.

205
00:18:34.011 --> 00:18:35.996
My mother was a different story.

206
00:18:37.097 --> 00:18:42.461
She was smart. cunning. and very cold.

207
00:18:43.813 --> 00:18:47.299
You know. I don't think she ever so much
as held my hand when I was a little boy.

208
00:18:47.942 --> 00:18:51.094
Naturally. she despised my father.
thought he was weak.

209
00:18:52.154 --> 00:18:55.599
And. yeah. sometimes so did I.

210
00:18:57.952 --> 00:19:03.857
As I got older. I began to understand
he wasn't weak at all.

211
00:19:05.251 --> 00:19:10.739
His was a... a quiet. subtle strength.

212
00:19:11.549 --> 00:19:12.699
That's all.

213
00:19:14.260 --> 00:19:17.871
I mean. to endure my mother
for as long as he did. Fuck me. Gee.

214
00:19:20.391 --> 00:19:26.228
Anyway. I like to think my understanding
of my own father means

215
00:19:26.312 --> 00:19:28.506
there's more of him in me than her.

216
00:19:29.858 --> 00:19:31.467
Why are you telling me this?

217
00:19:32.653 --> 00:19:36.974
Because. having never been one.
I have no advice for a new father.

218
00:19:37.366 --> 00:19:42.954
But for a confused son. you know.
I may be something of an expert.

219
00:19:43.038 --> 00:19:45.649
So. you ready?

220
00:19:48.294 --> 00:19:51.713
You've had a child
with a deranged. murderous woman.

221
00:19:51.797 --> 00:19:54.216
- Oh. fuck. Harlan.
- You know it. She is insane.

222
00:19:54.300 --> 00:19:58.662
But my point is
if any son ever needed a father.

223
00:19:59.722 --> 00:20:01.415
it's not you. you prick.

224
00:20:02.683 --> 00:20:05.586
It's him. It's your boy. All right?

225
00:20:07.062 --> 00:20:08.171
Your son.

226
00:20:15.196 --> 00:20:17.264
And that hasn't helped at all. has it?

227
00:20:18.991 --> 00:20:21.201
Uh... Not really. No.

228
00:20:21.285 --> 00:20:22.786
Well. if all else fails.

229
00:20:22.870 --> 00:20:25.814
let's ditch this piss
and get some good mulled wine.

230
00:20:26.665 --> 00:20:29.376
I'm not sure you're gonna find
something like that here.

231
00:20:29.460 --> 00:20:33.505
Shut up. Roddy. the good stuff. please.

232
00:20:33.589 --> 00:20:34.865
You got it. Harlan.

233
00:20:37.051 --> 00:20:40.787
- What?
- Told you. Still my city.

234
00:21:51.792 --> 00:21:52.985
Keep moving.

235
00:22:08.392 --> 00:22:10.002
Ayura. report.

236
00:22:16.817 --> 00:22:18.235
Two hundred strong.

237
00:22:18.319 --> 00:22:20.320
advancing quickly
from the north and south.

238
00:22:20.404 --> 00:22:21.780
Excellent.

239
00:22:21.864 --> 00:22:23.365
Attack formation.

240
00:22:25.326 --> 00:22:27.185
That won't be necessary.

241
00:22:30.247 --> 00:22:31.398
Oloman.

242
00:22:32.166 --> 00:22:33.317
Thirty heartbeats.

243
00:22:41.050 --> 00:22:42.342
They are almost on top of us.

244
00:22:42.426 --> 00:22:44.244
No one moves!

245
00:22:49.517 --> 00:22:51.101
Get ready to charge!

246
00:22:51.185 --> 00:22:54.254
- No! Stand your ground!
- What?

247
00:23:01.153 --> 00:23:04.114
If we do not fight. we will die!

248
00:23:04.198 --> 00:23:05.807
Not today.

249
00:23:08.327 --> 00:23:09.619
Ten heartbeats.

250
00:23:09.703 --> 00:23:12.914
My friends. prepare yourselves.

251
00:23:12.998 --> 00:23:14.650
For what?

252
00:23:32.351 --> 00:23:36.505
Ah.

253
00:24:01.297 --> 00:24:03.382
It's actually not as uncommon
as you think.

254
00:24:03.466 --> 00:24:05.884
- Thank you.
- I grew up in the foothills of the Cleves.

255
00:24:05.968 --> 00:24:11.515
and there was more than one grandmother
who was also her grandchild's aunt.

256
00:24:11.599 --> 00:24:18.463
In this case. the mother is also the aunt.
which I admit is a bit complicated.

257
00:24:19.023 --> 00:24:22.901
As the father is the mother's nephew.

258
00:24:22.985 --> 00:24:27.656
which would make Kofun
and his son cousins.

259
00:24:27.740 --> 00:24:31.284
No. wait. I think. Yes. that's right.

260
00:24:31.368 --> 00:24:35.606
And that makes you
the baby's aunt and cousin as well.

261
00:24:36.290 --> 00:24:38.542
Whew! If you think
this is complicated now.

262
00:24:38.626 --> 00:24:41.194
wait until someone has to
explain it all to that baby.

263
00:24:42.463 --> 00:24:44.423
I wonder what the baby should call me.

264
00:24:44.507 --> 00:24:47.300
Aunt Charlotte. Kind of a nice ring.

265
00:24:47.384 --> 00:24:49.553
- Aunt Char-Char.
- And these came in when?

266
00:24:49.637 --> 00:24:50.985
Just this morning.

267
00:25:23.254 --> 00:25:26.406
Edo understood the potential of sight

268
00:25:26.966 --> 00:25:29.660
and the glorious technology
it could unlock.

269
00:25:31.387 --> 00:25:35.182
Unfortunately. we were unable
to perfect our explosives

270
00:25:35.266 --> 00:25:37.042
before his march on Paya.

271
00:25:38.727 --> 00:25:42.381
If we had. my friend would still be here.

272
00:25:44.150 --> 00:25:48.720
I failed him.
and that failure haunts me every day.

273
00:25:50.948 --> 00:25:55.018
So. I will complete the task
he set for me.

274
00:25:56.704 --> 00:25:59.873
The Triangle was very opposed
to Edo's strategy when it came to vision.

275
00:25:59.957 --> 00:26:03.735
The Triangle.
They've gotten too comfortable.

276
00:26:04.378 --> 00:26:06.630
Their failure at Green hill Gap is
a perfect example

277
00:26:06.714 --> 00:26:09.449
of just how dangerous that can be for us.

278
00:26:10.634 --> 00:26:16.915
Edo beat his drum over and over again.
and they refused to hear it.

279
00:26:17.516 --> 00:26:19.810
But you believe they will hear you.

280
00:26:21.312 --> 00:26:27.676
Well. I think you'll agree
we now have a much louder drum.

281
00:26:30.988 --> 00:26:33.849
You were very loyal to Edo.

282
00:26:37.787 --> 00:26:43.358
And he protected you.
You and your special gift.

283
00:26:45.377 --> 00:26:46.486
Ah. yes.

284
00:26:47.797 --> 00:26:49.573
Edo had no secrets from me.

285
00:26:50.633 --> 00:26:52.409
And now I suppose neither do you.

286
00:26:54.136 --> 00:26:57.414
Together we can finish what Edo started.

287
00:26:58.557 --> 00:27:01.460
I'm assuming I can count on you. Wren?

288
00:27:04.730 --> 00:27:06.006
Of course. sir.

289
00:27:08.025 --> 00:27:13.013
I just... I'm not sure
what you're asking me to do.

290
00:27:13.405 --> 00:27:17.142
Oh. I'm not asking. I'm ordering you.

291
00:27:18.661 --> 00:27:21.580
The war with the Ganites
is as good as over.

292
00:27:21.664 --> 00:27:23.982
We must now
turn our attention to the east.

293
00:27:25.543 --> 00:27:26.652
Paya.

294
00:27:27.253 --> 00:27:30.756
Fertile lands. endless coal.

295
00:27:30.840 --> 00:27:35.869
and must I remind you.
the man who murdered our beloved Edo.

296
00:27:37.221 --> 00:27:40.666
You'll be happy to hear that my spies
have been tracking Baba Voss.

297
00:27:41.517 --> 00:27:45.462
And Edo will soon be properly avenged.

298
00:27:45.855 --> 00:27:51.260
So this all ends with us killing Baba Voss
and conquering Paya?

299
00:27:52.069 --> 00:27:54.763
No. That's where it begins.

300
00:27:56.282 --> 00:28:01.311
What lies beyond Paya? And beyond that?

301
00:28:02.997 --> 00:28:07.776
There are reports of cities
to be conquered in every direction.

302
00:28:08.294 --> 00:28:11.004
We now have a weapon
that makes us truly unstoppable.

303
00:28:11.088 --> 00:28:15.534
We will build the greatest empire
this world has ever known.

304
00:28:19.930 --> 00:28:22.583
Maddox.

305
00:28:24.310 --> 00:28:26.878
Sadly. I must leave you.

306
00:28:27.897 --> 00:28:31.466
This is Lieutenant Maddox.
my right-hand man.

307
00:28:32.860 --> 00:28:36.430
He doesn't say much.
which is one of his many attributes.

308
00:28:37.239 --> 00:28:41.977
He will help you finish your work here
and then escort you back to Trivantes.

309
00:28:44.163 --> 00:28:46.081
I should stay with my battalion.

310
00:28:46.165 --> 00:28:50.152
Oh. I think we both know
you are far too valuable for that.

311
00:28:50.711 --> 00:28:51.712
Mmm?

312
00:28:51.796 --> 00:28:55.407
Well. miles to go before I sleep.

313
00:29:09.688 --> 00:29:12.215
I'm telling you. I know what I saw.

314
00:29:12.775 --> 00:29:17.137
Maybe you did.
Or maybe you just wanted it to be true.

315
00:29:17.905 --> 00:29:19.656
There have been
no sighted people for so long.

316
00:29:19.740 --> 00:29:21.908
we cannot simply expect
to start finding them everywhere.

317
00:29:21.992 --> 00:29:24.186
Well. maybe there are more
than we know of.

318
00:29:24.662 --> 00:29:26.621
They just didn't want to be burned
as witches.

319
00:29:26.705 --> 00:29:28.065
Maybe they still don't.

320
00:29:28.707 --> 00:29:32.586
You cannot change the minds of the masses
with a simple decree like Sibeth believed.

321
00:29:32.670 --> 00:29:36.448
It will take years
for the unsighted to accept the sighted.

322
00:29:38.092 --> 00:29:41.053
It was our sight that helped save
the Payan kingdom at Green hill Gap.

323
00:29:41.137 --> 00:29:43.680
- It was the Hidden Tribes that saved us.
- I said helped.

324
00:29:43.764 --> 00:29:48.126
Look. whoever this Row Vano is.
you should leave him alone.

325
00:29:48.894 --> 00:29:52.297
If he wants to hide his sight.
then let him. I wish I could.

326
00:29:52.857 --> 00:29:54.483
How can you deny who you are?

327
00:29:54.567 --> 00:29:56.735
Because I'm not defined by
the fact that I can see.

328
00:29:56.819 --> 00:29:58.320
Of course you are.

329
00:29:58.404 --> 00:30:00.113
Y-You sound like Jerlamarel.

330
00:30:00.197 --> 00:30:02.866
- And you sound like an ass.
- Haniwa. that's enough.

331
00:30:02.950 --> 00:30:05.619
We finally have the power
to be able to build a world

332
00:30:05.703 --> 00:30:08.188
where people like us
don't have to live in fear.

333
00:30:10.791 --> 00:30:12.109
Don't you want that?

334
00:30:14.462 --> 00:30:15.946
If not for you. for your son?

335
00:30:21.594 --> 00:30:22.703
Hmm?

336
00:30:33.522 --> 00:30:35.257
Has he even seen his baby?

337
00:30:36.025 --> 00:30:37.442
I'm sure we can both understand

338
00:30:37.526 --> 00:30:39.886
this is not how he imagined
becoming a father.

339
00:30:40.362 --> 00:30:42.055
He will need time.

340
00:30:46.952 --> 00:30:48.620
Papa would make him take responsibility…

341
00:30:48.704 --> 00:30:49.705
…for his son.

342
00:30:49.789 --> 00:30:51.790
Well. he's not here. is he?

343
00:30:51.874 --> 00:30:52.999
And as far as I'm concerned.

344
00:30:53.083 --> 00:30:54.960
Baba is in no position to tell anyone
how to be a father.

345
00:30:55.044 --> 00:30:59.364
- He will come back! You know he will.
- All I know is that he left us.

346
00:31:00.424 --> 00:31:01.425
He left me.

347
00:31:01.509 --> 00:31:04.453
You left him first.

348
00:31:07.556 --> 00:31:10.642
You lied to him. to all of us.

349
00:31:10.726 --> 00:31:15.088
And then you just expected him
to accept all of this. What. your palace?

350
00:31:17.733 --> 00:31:18.734
Your new husband?

351
00:31:18.818 --> 00:31:21.053
What I did. I did for you.

352
00:31:22.488 --> 00:31:23.597
Maybe.

353
00:31:26.534 --> 00:31:31.146
But what you did destroyed him.
And I don't blame him for leaving.

354
00:31:36.669 --> 00:31:37.778
Haniwa!

355
00:33:11.096 --> 00:33:12.539
What's wrong. buddy?

356
00:33:13.808 --> 00:33:15.250
Are you a wolf?

357
00:33:19.814 --> 00:33:22.716
Okay. I'm here to help you.

358
00:33:25.361 --> 00:33:27.054
Please don't bite me.

359
00:33:27.822 --> 00:33:29.890
I don't wanna have to kill you.

360
00:33:36.705 --> 00:33:40.359
Good boy. Good boy. Oh. yes. good boy.

361
00:33:41.460 --> 00:33:44.363
What are you doing up here?

362
00:33:45.381 --> 00:33:47.491
What is that?

363
00:33:48.467 --> 00:33:51.720
Oh. yeah. What is this?

364
00:33:51.804 --> 00:33:54.389
It's okay.

365
00:33:54.473 --> 00:33:57.225
Yes. I'm gonna get this off.

366
00:33:57.309 --> 00:33:59.294
It's okay. It's okay.

367
00:33:59.687 --> 00:34:00.837
Yes. good boy.

368
00:34:02.314 --> 00:34:04.967
Yeah. Okay.

369
00:34:08.028 --> 00:34:11.073
I have a...
Oh. a little bit of food.

370
00:34:11.157 --> 00:34:13.350
Yeah. Okay.

371
00:34:13.784 --> 00:34:16.103
Tastes pretty good.

372
00:34:16.620 --> 00:34:18.205
Yeah. smell.

373
00:34:18.289 --> 00:34:21.525
Yeah. it's right there. There's more.

374
00:34:22.418 --> 00:34:24.544
There! No. no. no. no. no. Okay. okay.

375
00:34:24.628 --> 00:34:27.781
I'm gonna let you go now. Please don't
come at me. or I will kill you.

376
00:34:28.174 --> 00:34:29.174
Go.

377
00:35:45.960 --> 00:35:47.486
Ah. fuck off!

378
00:35:48.003 --> 00:35:50.364
You gonna help me up?

379
00:35:53.968 --> 00:35:55.827
No one could ever sneak up on you.

380
00:35:56.387 --> 00:35:58.163
No one's as noisy as you.

381
00:35:59.473 --> 00:36:01.375
One day. I will surprise you.

382
00:36:01.851 --> 00:36:03.335
That would be a surprise.

383
00:36:04.145 --> 00:36:05.562
Don't move.

384
00:36:05.646 --> 00:36:07.522
Do it. just do it. Do it.

385
00:36:07.606 --> 00:36:11.735
You ready?
Tradition is tradition. my friend.

386
00:36:11.819 --> 00:36:16.114
And you are the loser.

387
00:36:18.868 --> 00:36:23.647
- Oh. it stinks!
- I would think you'd be used to it by now.

388
00:36:26.625 --> 00:36:29.111
Your time is gonna come. Baba.

389
00:36:31.464 --> 00:36:33.657
- You done?
- For now.

390
00:36:34.382 --> 00:36:36.785
Good. Let's go climb.

391
00:36:37.178 --> 00:36:38.762
You just scared away dinner.

392
00:36:38.846 --> 00:36:40.555
I'm gonna have to go track down
another buck.

393
00:36:40.639 --> 00:36:43.584
Oh. We have enough meat.

394
00:36:44.268 --> 00:36:47.354
In the time you've been here.
you've managed to kill more deer

395
00:36:47.438 --> 00:36:49.021
than we could ever eat.

396
00:36:49.105 --> 00:36:51.216
Makes me wonder
what you're really chasing.

397
00:36:54.236 --> 00:36:56.655
Come on.
I can feel your dark thoughts from here.

398
00:36:58.616 --> 00:37:00.057
Let's go climb.

399
00:37:00.826 --> 00:37:04.996
Clear that shit out of your head.
Clear the shit off of my face.

400
00:37:07.248 --> 00:37:11.153
Let it out. That's right.

401
00:37:29.146 --> 00:37:31.965
You want some?

402
00:37:36.028 --> 00:37:37.262
No. thank you.

403
00:37:39.031 --> 00:37:40.933
It helps with the big questions.

404
00:37:42.326 --> 00:37:43.435
Like what?

405
00:37:44.495 --> 00:37:47.356
Like why you're here.

406
00:37:50.251 --> 00:37:52.377
It's because I belong nowhere else.

407
00:37:52.461 --> 00:37:53.695
You know that.

408
00:37:56.966 --> 00:37:59.968
You have spent your life running
and jumping

409
00:38:00.052 --> 00:38:04.081
and slashing and burning
in the service of others.

410
00:38:07.059 --> 00:38:08.752
Now you're alone. brother.

411
00:38:09.228 --> 00:38:11.463
Time to live in service to yourself.

412
00:38:24.827 --> 00:38:30.607
I have spent my life
trying to protect my family…

413
00:38:32.501 --> 00:38:34.987
But I always lead them into more danger.

414
00:38:36.422 --> 00:38:42.260
And I feel like I have cursed

415
00:38:42.344 --> 00:38:46.665
everyone that I love with death and war.

416
00:38:48.767 --> 00:38:50.961
You blame yourself for Edo.

417
00:38:54.482 --> 00:38:55.941
I did not mention him.

418
00:38:56.025 --> 00:38:57.426
Oh. he's always there.

419
00:38:58.652 --> 00:38:59.903
floating between your words.

420
00:38:59.987 --> 00:39:02.155
- We already talked about this.
- We have.

421
00:39:02.239 --> 00:39:07.311
but we will continue to talk about it
until it no longer has any power over you.

422
00:39:11.874 --> 00:39:13.734
Baba. I remember your father.

423
00:39:15.961 --> 00:39:18.530
He was a cruel fucker of a man.

424
00:39:19.548 --> 00:39:23.118
You became who you became.
and Edo became Edo.

425
00:39:25.346 --> 00:39:29.833
But at some point.
it's not your father's fault either.

426
00:39:30.518 --> 00:39:32.252
and it certainly isn't yours.

427
00:39:35.147 --> 00:39:37.883
We are responsible for who we become.

428
00:39:40.486 --> 00:39:42.404
And if climbing teaches you nothing else.

429
00:39:42.488 --> 00:39:45.057
it should teach you
your own insignificance.

430
00:39:45.449 --> 00:39:48.368
Even you. Baba Voss.

431
00:39:48.452 --> 00:39:53.148
are nothing more than a speck of shit
on the ass of a bug.

432
00:39:55.835 --> 00:39:57.236
You talk too much.

433
00:39:58.003 --> 00:40:01.281
Maybe it's the herbs.

434
00:40:28.409 --> 00:40:30.686
No! Go away!

435
00:40:31.370 --> 00:40:33.413
Shoo! Go! Leave me alone.

436
00:40:33.497 --> 00:40:35.957
- Your dog is hungry.
- He's not my dog.

437
00:40:36.041 --> 00:40:37.292
Tell him that.

438
00:40:37.376 --> 00:40:39.336
No!

439
00:40:39.420 --> 00:40:40.571
What's his name?

440
00:40:41.547 --> 00:40:43.006
I guess his name's "No."

441
00:40:43.090 --> 00:40:45.425
"No"? That's... That's not a name.

442
00:40:45.509 --> 00:40:47.511
That's the only thing he comes to.
isn't it?

443
00:40:47.595 --> 00:40:49.388
Go away!

444
00:40:49.472 --> 00:40:51.206
Going to be one confused dog.

445
00:40:52.349 --> 00:40:54.042
You should give him a nice name.

446
00:40:55.227 --> 00:40:56.353
You name him.

447
00:40:56.437 --> 00:40:57.713
He's not my dog.

448
00:40:58.105 --> 00:40:59.381
My love!

449
00:41:00.524 --> 00:41:02.801
- Ranger!
- Baba's got a dog.

450
00:41:03.235 --> 00:41:04.486
I don't have a dog!

451
00:41:09.533 --> 00:41:11.660
Ranger. you said you were bringing meat.

452
00:41:11.744 --> 00:41:13.120
He wanted fish.

453
00:41:13.204 --> 00:41:15.330
Yeah. it's better for your brain.

454
00:41:15.414 --> 00:41:17.999
The herbs you smoke have taken
what is left of your brain.

455
00:41:18.083 --> 00:41:20.110
Only the bad parts.

456
00:41:20.878 --> 00:41:22.613
Baba thinks I'm wise. don't you. Baba?

457
00:41:23.088 --> 00:41:24.698
I think I should remain silent.

458
00:41:25.174 --> 00:41:27.050
- I think you should leave.
- Lu.

459
00:41:27.134 --> 00:41:28.468
Don't "Lu" me!

460
00:41:28.552 --> 00:41:31.471
You told me he would stay
for a few days. and it's been months.

461
00:41:31.555 --> 00:41:32.556
Here we go.

462
00:41:32.640 --> 00:41:36.293
He brought about the death
of the Alkenny. my people.

463
00:41:37.061 --> 00:41:40.230
That was the Witchfinders. not Baba.

464
00:41:40.314 --> 00:41:43.175
But you ask me
to hear his voice every day.

465
00:41:47.488 --> 00:41:48.889
I'm not asking.

466
00:42:01.919 --> 00:42:06.281
Do you even remember the Alkenny.
Baba Voss?

467
00:42:13.347 --> 00:42:14.581
Every day.

468
00:42:37.037 --> 00:42:38.038
Chet-Chet!

469
00:42:38.122 --> 00:42:39.648
Lion.

470
00:42:43.085 --> 00:42:46.405
You shouldn't be traveling up here
by yourself. This is wolf country.

471
00:42:46.797 --> 00:42:48.407
You shouldn't be here either.

472
00:42:48.924 --> 00:42:51.009
No one should. except maybe the wolves.

473
00:42:51.093 --> 00:42:52.386
This is our home.

474
00:42:52.470 --> 00:42:54.054
A guest should show more respect.

475
00:42:54.138 --> 00:42:57.140
especially one who shows up
uninvited the way you do.

476
00:42:57.224 --> 00:42:59.017
I don't wanna be in this
sad little hiding spot

477
00:42:59.101 --> 00:43:00.811
- any more than you want me here.
- Bow Lion...

478
00:43:00.895 --> 00:43:02.043
We're not hiding.

479
00:43:02.480 --> 00:43:05.549
We're just not wearing the old knots
and bones anymore.

480
00:43:07.109 --> 00:43:10.429
Nations. kingdoms. tribes.
they're all the same.

481
00:43:10.988 --> 00:43:14.866
Can't be a part of any of them
without giving up a piece of your soul

482
00:43:14.950 --> 00:43:16.118
you can never get back.

483
00:43:16.202 --> 00:43:18.937
You don't believe any of this.
do you. Baba?

484
00:43:20.247 --> 00:43:22.232
You were a great leader.

485
00:43:24.418 --> 00:43:27.546
A great leader responsible
for ending an entire tribe.

486
00:43:27.630 --> 00:43:28.755
That wasn't your fault.

487
00:43:28.839 --> 00:43:31.950
No? Whose was it?

488
00:43:37.389 --> 00:43:38.498
Baba?

489
00:43:40.559 --> 00:43:42.044
Go home. Bow Lion.

490
00:43:43.896 --> 00:43:45.005
Please.

491
00:43:49.068 --> 00:43:51.929
I will. When you do.

492
00:43:57.118 --> 00:43:59.911
I thought you promised your mother
you would stop stalking this man.

493
00:43:59.995 --> 00:44:02.539
She insisted. I didn't promise.

494
00:44:02.623 --> 00:44:05.834
Oh. Well. if your mother is queen.
and you disobey her.

495
00:44:05.918 --> 00:44:07.653
can you be hung for treason?

496
00:44:08.337 --> 00:44:09.838
Not if she doesn't find out.

497
00:44:09.922 --> 00:44:11.673
Treason or not. this is a bad idea.

498
00:44:11.757 --> 00:44:14.217
Like all of you. I served the monarchy

499
00:44:14.301 --> 00:44:16.161
in the name of the God Flame.

500
00:44:17.638 --> 00:44:18.997
I fought for them.

501
00:44:20.432 --> 00:44:21.833
I bled for them.

502
00:44:22.560 --> 00:44:24.336
And they betrayed me.

503
00:44:26.272 --> 00:44:28.173
They betrayed all of us.

504
00:44:29.942 --> 00:44:32.861
Queen Kane betrayed us.

505
00:44:35.865 --> 00:44:39.351
Tamacti Jun betrayed us.

506
00:44:40.494 --> 00:44:44.106
and the so-called Queen Maghra betrays us.

507
00:44:44.498 --> 00:44:47.918
twisting the word of God
for her own purposes.

508
00:44:48.002 --> 00:44:51.572
Down with the queen.

509
00:44:52.590 --> 00:44:54.324
And so it falls to us.

510
00:44:55.384 --> 00:44:56.952
the Payan people.

511
00:44:58.512 --> 00:45:00.956
to serve the true word of God

512
00:45:02.099 --> 00:45:04.793
by continuing to drive out
the evil of sight.

513
00:45:06.312 --> 00:45:08.922
until the monarchy comes to their senses.

514
00:45:10.900 --> 00:45:12.134
Shiloh.

515
00:45:13.402 --> 00:45:14.761
let's have the witch.

516
00:45:15.237 --> 00:45:17.781
No. please let me go!
You are making a mistake.

517
00:45:17.865 --> 00:45:20.200
I am not a witch! I am not sighted!

518
00:45:20.284 --> 00:45:21.702
- Liar!
- Come on.

519
00:45:21.786 --> 00:45:24.371
We know you can see.
You deal in the devil's magic.

520
00:45:24.455 --> 00:45:27.524
I cannot see. I swear to you.
I am not a witch!

521
00:45:31.837 --> 00:45:33.880
- They can't do this.
- There's too many of them.

522
00:45:33.964 --> 00:45:36.675
- You're sworn to protect the sighted.
- That's what I'm doing. Let's go.

523
00:45:36.759 --> 00:45:38.427
- What about him?
- We go now!

524
00:45:38.511 --> 00:45:41.330
Stop this! Stop!

525
00:45:43.641 --> 00:45:45.208
He is an innocent man.

526
00:45:46.268 --> 00:45:48.045
And what proof do you have of that?

527
00:45:52.233 --> 00:45:53.900
Because I can see his eyes.

528
00:45:53.984 --> 00:45:55.694
Okay. shit.

529
00:45:55.778 --> 00:45:58.530
I am Princess Haniwa.
daughter of Queen Maghra.

530
00:45:58.614 --> 00:46:01.199
and in her name.
I command you to let the man go.

531
00:46:03.786 --> 00:46:05.412
The witch child of Queen Maghra.

532
00:46:06.705 --> 00:46:09.666
You do understand
we are burning witches here.

533
00:46:09.750 --> 00:46:11.568
not taking orders from them.

534
00:46:12.586 --> 00:46:13.587
Grab her!

535
00:46:13.671 --> 00:46:14.921
I got her!

536
00:46:15.005 --> 00:46:16.156
Please. please. please.

537
00:46:17.299 --> 00:46:18.842
Eyes! Take her eyes!

538
00:46:18.926 --> 00:46:22.012
In the name of the God Flame
and all that is holy…

539
00:46:22.096 --> 00:46:24.222
…we send your corrupt soul

540
00:46:24.306 --> 00:46:26.166
back to the devil himself!

541
00:46:41.198 --> 00:46:44.034
Stay back! Haniwa!

542
00:46:44.118 --> 00:46:45.310
I'm here.

543
00:46:46.745 --> 00:46:47.980
I see you!

544
00:46:48.539 --> 00:46:49.982
I see all of you!

545
00:46:51.167 --> 00:46:52.609
You'll pay for this!

546
00:46:53.961 --> 00:46:57.714
Reports are coming in from the border.
I will keep the military on high alert.

547
00:46:57.798 --> 00:47:00.701
Our concerns are justified.
Captain Gosset.

548
00:47:01.177 --> 00:47:03.637
How do we know that handing
the Trivantians Sibeth's head

549
00:47:03.721 --> 00:47:04.846
will guarantee the peace?

550
00:47:04.930 --> 00:47:07.682
- Hmm.
- This is Trivantes we speak of.

551
00:47:07.766 --> 00:47:08.892
There's no reason to believe

552
00:47:08.976 --> 00:47:10.894
the Trivantians
will go back on their word.

553
00:47:10.978 --> 00:47:12.562
You cannot be certain of that.

554
00:47:12.646 --> 00:47:15.899
No. but I know what happens
for certain if we decline.

555
00:47:15.983 --> 00:47:19.152
I've spent the past months
haggling with Ambassador Trovere.

556
00:47:19.236 --> 00:47:20.904
and I believe her to be truthful.

557
00:47:20.988 --> 00:47:22.072
And if you're wrong?

558
00:47:22.156 --> 00:47:24.950
We have increased production
on Lord Harlan's orders.

559
00:47:25.034 --> 00:47:27.644
If the truce fails.
we will be ready for the armories.

560
00:47:28.454 --> 00:47:31.857
I have received word that
Ambassador Trovere will be arriving soon.

561
00:47:32.249 --> 00:47:33.417
How soon?

562
00:47:33.501 --> 00:47:36.211
Her delegation should be at the city gates
by the rise of the God Flame.

563
00:47:36.295 --> 00:47:38.196
- What?
- They're moving swiftly.

564
00:47:38.631 --> 00:47:39.798
Maybe it's a good sign.

565
00:47:39.882 --> 00:47:42.551
The Trivantians are not
the only danger we face.

566
00:47:42.635 --> 00:47:45.495
There are reports of religious riots
on an almost daily basis now.

567
00:47:47.139 --> 00:47:49.558
Your Majesty's continued support
of the queen's edict on sight

568
00:47:49.642 --> 00:47:50.892
continues to divide the people.

569
00:47:50.976 --> 00:47:54.479
Why are we listening to this commoner?
He shouldn't even be here.

570
00:47:54.563 --> 00:47:58.108
He serves. as you do.
at the pleasure of the queen.

571
00:47:58.192 --> 00:48:01.153
Why don't we just put some Trivantians
on the council?

572
00:48:01.237 --> 00:48:04.740
They'd likely be more productive
than certain entitled Payans.

573
00:48:04.824 --> 00:48:05.824
Lord Harlan...

574
00:48:05.908 --> 00:48:07.184
Don't forget.

575
00:48:07.576 --> 00:48:11.580
it was Queen Maghra who negotiated this
peace when none was thought possible.

576
00:48:11.664 --> 00:48:16.001
And do I really need to remind you
that nine months ago.

577
00:48:16.085 --> 00:48:19.963
Lady Benik.
our people were dying on the battlefield.

578
00:48:20.047 --> 00:48:23.216
and it's only thanks to the wisdom
and skill of this queen

579
00:48:23.300 --> 00:48:25.702
that we're not all slaves now.

580
00:48:26.345 --> 00:48:30.123
We have a Trivantian problem.
We have a local problem.

581
00:48:30.558 --> 00:48:33.502
Sibeth's death will solve the first.

582
00:48:34.228 --> 00:48:35.729
I'll deal with the second.

583
00:48:35.813 --> 00:48:38.840
Killing Sibeth is more dangerous
than you might think.

584
00:48:39.525 --> 00:48:42.069
Some people still believe in her prophecy.

585
00:48:42.153 --> 00:48:44.596
Her death could martyr her
and cause an uprising.

586
00:48:44.989 --> 00:48:47.683
Queen Maghra. do you have no opinion?

587
00:48:48.200 --> 00:48:51.270
You have not spoken
since the council came to session.

588
00:48:56.167 --> 00:48:57.751
I am sorry if it takes me a moment

589
00:48:57.835 --> 00:49:00.487
to figure out
how to best kill my own sister.

590
00:49:01.547 --> 00:49:04.549
We merely have to let the people
think Sibeth died of complications

591
00:49:04.633 --> 00:49:05.842
from childbirth.

592
00:49:05.926 --> 00:49:09.846
Some already know she survived the birth.
The truth will come out.

593
00:49:09.930 --> 00:49:11.807
First rule of government. Torrance.

594
00:49:11.891 --> 00:49:15.043
Tell a lie enough times.
it becomes fact to the people.

595
00:49:16.353 --> 00:49:20.565
If we don't make peace with Trivantes.
it won't matter what our people think.

596
00:49:20.649 --> 00:49:21.967
They'll be dead.

597
00:49:23.694 --> 00:49:26.680
My sister got us into this war.

598
00:49:27.448 --> 00:49:31.576
If giving them her head will get us
out of it. then I must consider it.

599
00:49:31.660 --> 00:49:33.912
- Your Highness...
- I said I will consider it.

600
00:49:33.996 --> 00:49:35.704
This council is adjourned.

601
00:49:59.939 --> 00:50:01.673
There's something you need to know.

602
00:50:04.360 --> 00:50:06.970
The Trivantians want a public trial.

603
00:50:08.572 --> 00:50:12.434
I don't know. The Triangle need
to declare some kind of victory here.

604
00:50:14.411 --> 00:50:15.854
They want her alive?

605
00:50:17.748 --> 00:50:18.857
Yeah.

606
00:50:20.209 --> 00:50:22.402
They will spend years torturing her.

607
00:50:23.462 --> 00:50:24.780
Most likely.

608
00:50:27.174 --> 00:50:30.452
Consider the alternative.
There might not be another way.

609
00:50:38.352 --> 00:50:39.795
It seems to me

610
00:50:40.604 --> 00:50:44.132
you're waiting for an act of God
to take the decision away from you.

611
00:50:46.152 --> 00:50:51.556
But maybe it was that act of God
that put you in this spot to begin with.

612
00:50:56.787 --> 00:50:59.565
It would be a grave error
to go to war for this.

613
00:51:01.625 --> 00:51:04.111
I think you know in your heart
what needs to be done.

614
00:51:05.796 --> 00:51:06.905
Yes.

615
00:51:10.134 --> 00:51:12.177
There's no need for you
to be directly involved.

616
00:51:12.261 --> 00:51:14.538
I'll handle Trovere and the delivery.

617
00:51:16.140 --> 00:51:17.833
I'll let you know when it's done.

618
00:51:20.478 --> 00:51:23.171
I wanted so badly not to be like her.

619
00:51:33.282 --> 00:51:34.850
You're nothing like her.

620
00:52:21.956 --> 00:52:24.399
Ambassador Trovere. welcome back.

621
00:52:24.792 --> 00:52:26.026
Lord Harlan.

622
00:52:26.669 --> 00:52:29.671
I assume your people know by now
where to set up camp.

623
00:52:29.755 --> 00:52:32.299
You will wanna wash up. get some rest.

624
00:52:32.383 --> 00:52:35.260
Where's the queen?
Will she not be greeting me?

625
00:52:35.344 --> 00:52:39.831
The queen has entrusted me
with the resolution of this matter.

626
00:52:41.100 --> 00:52:42.292
Has she now?

627
00:52:44.186 --> 00:52:45.420
Yes. she has.

628
00:52:46.188 --> 00:52:47.339
How exciting.

629
00:52:48.399 --> 00:52:49.925
And is it resolved?

630
00:52:50.943 --> 00:52:52.611
I'll have it resolved by dinner.

631
00:52:52.695 --> 00:52:57.099
Well. then. I'm very much
anticipating our dinner.

632
00:52:59.034 --> 00:53:00.269
As am I.

633
00:53:04.623 --> 00:53:05.899
Set up camp!

634
00:53:08.502 --> 00:53:09.611
Fall out!

635
00:53:33.277 --> 00:53:35.654
- Ready for this?
- Stupid question.

636
00:53:35.738 --> 00:53:37.764
Right. Make way.

637
00:53:39.366 --> 00:53:41.076
Stand down. Tamacti Jun.

638
00:53:41.160 --> 00:53:44.313
Yes. Tamacti Jun. Do stand down.

639
00:53:45.080 --> 00:53:46.873
Don't worry about the nasty man.

640
00:53:46.957 --> 00:53:51.128
He may make some scary noises.
but he's empty inside. Weak and hollow.

641
00:53:51.212 --> 00:53:52.629
I'd be quiet. Sibeth.

642
00:53:52.713 --> 00:53:54.965
Maghra? What are you doing here?

643
00:53:55.049 --> 00:53:58.452
I don't know exactly.
but we will not be handing her over today.

644
00:53:59.053 --> 00:54:01.304
You would defend her
at the cost of your own kingdom?

645
00:54:01.388 --> 00:54:02.389
It's not her kingdom.

646
00:54:02.473 --> 00:54:04.975
A queen who gives away her own sister
in the name of peace

647
00:54:05.059 --> 00:54:07.269
will appear weak and desperate.

648
00:54:07.353 --> 00:54:09.087
Not this sister.

649
00:54:09.772 --> 00:54:11.506
Poor Tamacti Jun.

650
00:54:12.024 --> 00:54:15.010
He'll have to take his revenge
some other day.

651
00:54:17.571 --> 00:54:18.972
Let me take her.

652
00:54:20.324 --> 00:54:21.433
Please.

653
00:54:23.160 --> 00:54:24.311
I'm sorry.

654
00:54:27.832 --> 00:54:30.567
Maghra.
I do believe your general is sulking.

655
00:54:39.969 --> 00:54:41.662
You think I'm making a mistake?

656
00:54:42.054 --> 00:54:43.288
Oh. you know me.

657
00:54:43.681 --> 00:54:46.875
Enormous changes at the last minute
are my stock-in-trade.

658
00:54:48.519 --> 00:54:49.628
Thank you.

659
00:54:50.729 --> 00:54:52.005
That said.

660
00:54:52.940 --> 00:54:56.218
we do now find ourselves
in something of a predicament.

661
00:54:58.779 --> 00:55:03.267
I know the ambassador
is more than a little fond of you.

662
00:55:06.871 --> 00:55:07.980
Um…

663
00:55:10.291 --> 00:55:13.085
Yeah. it... it seems…

664
00:55:13.169 --> 00:55:15.821
…she's not completely immune to my charms.

665
00:55:18.799 --> 00:55:21.952
Well. then. you'll have to be
exceedingly charming.

666
00:56:16.816 --> 00:56:19.109
You have been here for two days.
Don't you have somewhere to be?

667
00:56:19.193 --> 00:56:20.385
Don't you?

668
00:56:22.947 --> 00:56:24.848
I'm no longer needed.

669
00:56:25.366 --> 00:56:27.309
Your family will always need you. Baba.

670
00:56:27.868 --> 00:56:29.327
We will not talk about that. Lion.

671
00:56:29.411 --> 00:56:31.288
Then let's talk about something else.

672
00:56:31.372 --> 00:56:34.458
The tribes answered your call
to fight at Green hill Gap.

673
00:56:34.542 --> 00:56:36.626
Now there are many orphans
without a parent

674
00:56:36.710 --> 00:56:38.545
to teach them how to hunt and track.

675
00:56:38.629 --> 00:56:39.629
No one to guide them.

676
00:56:41.090 --> 00:56:44.551
I have spent enough time
raising other men's children.

677
00:56:44.635 --> 00:56:45.869
Baba?

678
00:56:46.387 --> 00:56:48.497
Bow Lion. go home!

679
00:56:54.478 --> 00:56:55.712
What is that?

680
00:57:01.360 --> 00:57:02.444
We're not alone.

681
00:57:02.528 --> 00:57:04.096
Baba?

682
00:57:05.614 --> 00:57:06.890
Baba Voss?

683
00:57:08.617 --> 00:57:09.893
Do you know him?

684
00:57:11.328 --> 00:57:14.331
Baba Voss!

685
00:57:14.415 --> 00:57:15.524
Hello?

686
00:57:16.834 --> 00:57:18.193
Are you there?

687
00:57:18.586 --> 00:57:20.571
I'm not really asking.

688
00:57:22.256 --> 00:57:23.782
I know you're there.

689
00:57:24.383 --> 00:57:27.411
Our trackers followed your friend
from the tribes.

690
00:57:27.845 --> 00:57:28.954
What?

691
00:57:29.513 --> 00:57:31.348
Baba...

692
00:57:31.432 --> 00:57:35.936
Did you really think we'd let the murder
of Edo go unpunished?

693
00:57:36.020 --> 00:57:38.897
Give me the butcher.
Grab your staff. We fight.

694
00:57:38.981 --> 00:57:40.591
He was not my brother.

695
00:57:41.734 --> 00:57:43.443
but I loved him like one.

696
00:57:43.527 --> 00:57:46.680
And it is that love that brings me here.

697
00:57:47.156 --> 00:57:48.932
to the brother who killed him.

698
00:57:49.450 --> 00:57:53.103
to end your life
and bring peace to his spirit.

699
00:57:54.038 --> 00:57:56.915
I can't hear you. You should come closer.

700
00:57:58.959 --> 00:58:01.153
I'm closer than you think. Baba.

701
00:58:01.545 --> 00:58:04.948
And you. you're already dead.

702
00:58:05.841 --> 00:58:08.343
You just haven't the sense
to lie down yet.

703
00:58:08.427 --> 00:58:12.623
You killed your father.
and now your brother.

704
00:58:13.140 --> 00:58:17.419
Tell me. is there anyone in your family
you haven't killed?

705
00:58:18.395 --> 00:58:19.546
Your wife?

706
00:58:20.731 --> 00:58:22.257
Your children?

707
00:58:23.567 --> 00:58:28.722
As you are but moments
from your own messy death…

708
00:58:30.950 --> 00:58:31.950
I give you my word.

709
00:58:32.034 --> 00:58:36.663
I will track them down
and cut their throats on your behalf.

710
00:58:39.278 --> 00:58:40.821
Lion!

711
00:58:41.305 --> 00:59:41.685
